Use the repository structure deliberately:
- `src/app` is for routes and layouts only.
- `src/modules` owns domain logic.
- `src/components/ui` owns reusable primitives.
- `src/components/layout` owns shells and wrappers.
- `src/components/branding` owns shared brand pieces.
- `src/lib` owns infrastructure helpers.
- `src/styles` owns tokens and global styles.
- Route groups must stay clear:
  - `(public)` for public shell and internal previews.
  - `(auth)` for sign-in, sign-up, and auth stubs.
  - `(platform)` for authenticated user shell.
  - `admin` for admin shell.
- Authentication logic belongs in `src/modules/auth` and `src/app/api/auth/*`, not in page files.
- Session access for shells must be centralized in `src/modules/auth/shell.tsx`.

Keep modules isolated:
- Do not move domain logic into components.
- Do not let page files become orchestration layers.
- Do not duplicate the same logic in multiple routes.
